	          <h2>Magnetic Tornadoes</h2>
	          <p>Mercury has a global magnetic field.</p>
			  <p>Its magnetic field has developed leaks that can allow the flow of solar wind, which has its own magnetic field.</p>
			  <p>Occasionaly the result is a funnelling of magnetic fields into a magnetic tornado.</p>
			  <p>Magnetic tornadoes allow solar wind plasma to directly hit Mercury's surface, blasting atoms into Mercury's exosphere.</p>
			</section>
